description:
All incidental video clips and sound effects found in the video game Constructor (1997). The video has been upscaled with nearest neighbor algorithm to compensate for video compression.

Win, Lose and Intro FMVs: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QH0Q5yded0s

Extraction tools:
constructor-fil: https://github.com/jimmypw/constructor-fil
fli2gif: https://github.com/bovine/fli2gif
and some custom batch scripts to perform bulk actions

comments.text: I added subtitles to this video for accessibility and your enjoyment :)
comments.author: @PAKTC

comments.text: This looks like the kind of dreams I used to have as a kid in the early 2000s after falling asleep to Jimmy Neutron. Good times.
comments.author: @rottenapple_

comments.text: I've never heard of this game, but some of these are fucking terrifying.
comments.author: @chitan1362

comments.text: If you thought that these were terrifying, as a kid, I never got really far into the game, so I would repeatedly see the game over FMV, which appears when you fail the main objective, one of the council missions or get too many black marks: https://youtube.com/clip/UgkxiAUmSwsHZX786-pTinT6SWTrTwOiFAqi?si=xIehIJojxy4yFMyW (this one's from the PS1 version, but it's basically the same on DOS version)
comments.author: @PAKTC
